author: Ron Moshier
title: Proctor football earns share of Class AA-2 title
text: Follow @@OD_Moshier Posted Oct. 17, 2015 at 6:21 PM Jamarious Morgan rushed for 183 yards on 18 carries and scored three touchdowns as Thomas R. Proctor High School’s football team earned a share of the Section III Class AA-2 title with a 43-35 victory over Fayetteville-Manlius in Saturday’s regular-season finale at D’Alessandro Stadium. Nick Abraham and Logan Wilcox also had touchdown runs for the Raiders (4-1, 6-1), who shared the AA-2 title with Baldwinsville and Cicero-North Syracuse. The Section III playoff pairings will be announced Sunday, but Proctor’s first-year head coach Steve Strife said he believes the Raiders will be a No. 2 seed and will host Nottingham (4-3) in a Class AA quarterfinal game at 1:30 p.m. next Saturday.
